<br>
Being able to raid Kael arena in an alliance raid does not count as a 2nd tier guild.  2nd tier guilds take down boss mobs like AoW and Trakkanon with their guild members alone.  There are a very few 1st tier guilds on Vazaelle with CC and PO being two of them, and there certainly are not many 2nd tier guilds either.  There are a LOT of 3rd tier guilds though, and that's the challenge... making it from 3rd tier to 2nd tier.<br>
<br>
Believe me, I like Tribal Fury, but until you can logon on, say in guild chat &quot;Trakkanon is up, assemble at zone line in 15 minutes,&quot; and take him down with your guild alone, your not close to 2nd tier yet.<br>
<br>
By the way, 2nd tier guilds typically don't have many, if any, members under level 60, and when they do, it's usually one of the members alts that is like level 56+.<br>
<br>
Personally, I don't know why anybody is shocked by the requirements that PO is putting on this thread.  Everybody knew <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>BEFORE</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> PoP even came out that to be in a 1st tier guild you had to be level 60 with a certain number of AA points.  If anything, people should be glad that Sony added 5 new levels to the level cap because now you can ding level 65 with NO AA points and you get considered over a level 60 with AA points because they over looked the AA points for the extra 5 levels.  These lofty member requirements are nothing new to EQ.<br>
<br>
I guess I can say that I gained a lot of knowledge from my years with Exodus Zek because I thought all of this stuff was common knowledge until this thread came up.<br>
