<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> My original post was about loyalty to the guild that got you there vs abandoning that guild with a long exodus of peeps leaving to join the next &quot;tier&quot; up. Seems to me that it is just a shame is all. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It really isn't something that happens to every guild.  It only happens to guilds where a good majority of their members are getting close to the upper end of the game AND want to see the end game.  They aren't leaving you to diss your guild or say that you suck.  Instead, they are just leaving your guild because they have a very lofty goal that they want to *TRY* to achieve, and they know that the only way they will get to *ATTEMPT* that goal is by being in a 2nd or 1st tier guild.  For instance, I know that I will never get to see the Emperor as long as I am the leader of Jemand Verbieten because Jemand Verbieten is just a small private guild.  We don't even consider ourselves a 3rd tier guild.  A lot of my members are very capable of being in good 3rd tier guilds, but they choose to be in JV for its fun atmosphere.  If any of my members decided that they wanted to see the end game after the turned level 60, I would not be against their decission, and I would support their decission whole heartedly.  Hell, for that matter, if all of my members quit tomorrow, I wouldn't be all that upset because it would mean that I could go back to actually having fun playing EQ instead of having to worry about keeping everybody happy<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  hahaha... <br>
